message: A) It isn't sourced. It rolls to SEPTA's front page B) blend or hybrid systems are not hard to categorize. They were intentionally built as middle ground systems between traditional subway and commuter rail. The MBTA does not operate such a system. Please allow this correction to stand
Relevant and will provide source. Please allow SOME information.
The MBTA does not operate all types of rail service. It does not have a hybrid or blend service. BART, DART, MARTA, DC, PATH
The MBTA does not have a commuter-subway blend line (PATH, DC Metro, MARTA, etc.)

I inquired if Conifer was part of the Green Line Extension (GLX) construction team. In response, Conifer has tried to apply every negative label for each edit tied to the GLX. I have also made changes to the MBTA South Coast Rail page that are similar to the other pages, yet Conifer has not attacked me on that page. I saw errors on each page and started to edit. I regret participating.
Untrue. Foy was a "Super-Secretary" under Romney. Foy was in charge of transportation. Romney's secretary of transportation reported to Foy
Outdated Map. Need To Show Upcoming 2023 Route Via Middleborough
Bridge closure criticism is in line with station closure criticism. Boston Magazine feature article framed major GLX gentrification concern
The lack of mitigation and poor scheduling would fall under the term "sloppy". Will change wording and divide. Conifer. Are you part of the GLX team?
Read The Notes. Read The Cited Information
GLX is a Big Dig Air Quality Mitigation Project That Cut Down 1000 Trees. The GLX Subsidy Is Extraordinarily High For LRT.
A $23 Million Per Year Subsidy For 4 Miles of LRT Is Very Notable. The MBTA Red Line Subsidy Is Nominal In Comparison. The NEC (Amtrak) Makes Money
Added $23 Million Operating Subsidy Note To Criticisms
$1.08 billion is the low bid number minus cost overrun $ for the state's $1.3 billion section of the FFGA: which includes $1 billion from the feds, and adds up to over $2 billion
